                    "company": "TenneT TSO B.V.",
                    "description": "Fueled by an interest in the sustainability challenges of the energy sector, I did a 4\u00bd-month-long internship at TenneT, a transmission system operator in the Netherlands and a large part of Germany. My main activities were related to the following topics: \n\n\u2022 Energy efficiency. I conducted a study into the underlying reasons for the unusually high energy consumption levels of several high-voltage substations, and identified opportunities for reducing energy use. \n\u2022 Circularity. In order to kick-start lifecycle thinking within the company, I assessed the waste flows produced by the demolition of a 110kV substation. Here, I collected data on the material composition of substation components (by asking suppliers for \u2018material passports\u2019), calculated the total volume and scrap value of the materials on the substation, and made recommendations for TenneT\u2019s waste policies and practices.\n\nOther tasks included:\n\u2022 Assisting in writing the proposal for the opening session of the CIGRE 2018 convention on climate change.\n\u2022 Calculating the total mobility footprint of TenneT employees in the Netherlands and Germany (for the 2017 Annual Report).\n\u2022 Creating a CSR-themed puzzle for the 2018 TenneT Contractor Forums.",
