            "description": "Together with musicians from Poland, Israel and Nepal, I was part of the band 'Happy Villlage Orchestra', where I played guitar and various percussions, and also set up the Dutch crowd-funding campaign for the project. Happy Village Orchestra was established in the context of the 'Music at the End of the World' project. The goal of this project was to facilitate cross-cultural learning and to provide entertainment for some of the poorest and most vulnerable people in Nepal. In total, our band played some 20 shows in villages around Pokhara, Annapurna and Dhaulagiri. Furthermore, we built a recording studio in Henjakot, where we made a full-length album with our own compositions, which is available on:\n\n- Bandcamp: https://happyvillageorchestra.bandcamp.com/\n- Spotify: https://open.spotify.com/album/7kSFKpY013BTORPzuRYUXL?si=SDRTSkrARzKDbtfwDpmEBA"
